<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2011-08-10</DATELINE><TITLE>Evaluation of Two Magnetic-Bead-Based Viral Nucleic Acid Purification Kits and Three Real-Time Reverse Transcription-PCR Reagent Systems in Two TaqMan Assays for Equine Arteritis Virus Detection in Semen</TITLE><BODY>This study showed that under specifically defined conditions with respect to nucleic acid extraction method and testing reagents, a previously described real-time reverse transcription-PCR (rRT-PCR) assay (T1 assay) provides sensitivity equal to or higher than that of virus isolation for the detection of equine arteritis virus in semen.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>